Articles.Content: I'll have a guess that youre running out of memory.....you running 32bit version with mods, try without the mods and attach logs again if problem persists.

On 11/13/2016 at 6:11 AM, Skyline Studios said:

2048 MB user address space [93 MB free].

This is the most important line.  On 32 bit windows each program can only use a max of 2 GB of memory and this includes the size of the exe and all the DLLs that it loads.  In the case of KSP, this means that it can only allocate about 1.7 GB before it will die.  There have always been issues where the amount of memory it uses increases and this will always, eventually, cause the game to crash on 32 bit windows.

There are various things you can do to help.  The best solution is to upgrade to a 64 bit version of windows (yes, even with only 4 GB of memory this will make a big difference, as even the 32 bit version of the game can use about 3.5 GB of memory on 64 bit windows).  The next best things is to do everything possible to reduce the amount of memory the game is using.  The first thing to try is to reduce the texture resolution in the settings as far as possible and see what effect that has.  There are also two command line options, -force-d3d11 and -force-glcore, either of which used to reduce the memory use considerably, though I don't know for certain they still have the same effect with KSP 1.2.  Keep an eye on how much memory KSP is using and restart the game when it gets too high (if you keep an eye on it you'll soon get to know what too high is for your particular system).
